pageTitle: Album Sales Charts - Week Ending September 5th - Rap Basement
TableContextTimeStampAfterTable: {4995=Posted by Jason on September 8, 2010 & filed under Sales Charts.}
textBeforeTable: Usher's new album drops nine spots to 13th while Drake's "Thank Me Later" debut album continues to move units with 19,000+, putting his total to 1.03 million copies. BoB's new album also continues to sell landing at 46th.            Eminem continues to be the top selling rapper this week as his "Recovery" album keeps its number 3 spot with close to 100,000 copies sold, putting his total so far at 2.42 million copies, while R&B singer Fantasia's new "Back To Me" falls to number 5 with over 40,000 albums sold. Posted by Jason on September 8, 2010 & filed under Sales Charts.
